=93 but, he writes, =E2=80=9Cit comes at a cost: no universal set of facts =
exists.=E2=80=9D
Nothing exists except in its interactions with other things. Everything is =
a web of relations.
According to Rovelli, =E2=80=9CA single equation (Heisenberg=E2=80=99s unce=
rtainty principle: =CE=94X=CE=94P =E2=89=A5 =E2=84=8F/2) codes quantum theo=
ry:=C2=A0
It implies that the world is not continuous but granular.=C2=A0
There is no infinite in going towards the small: things cannot get infinite=
ly smaller.
It tells us the future is not determined by the present.=C2=A0
It tells us that physical things have property in relation to other physica=
l things, and that these properties make sense only when things interact.=
=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
It=E2=80=99s hard to believe that this is how things work, but quantum theo=
ry remains undefeated. It=E2=80=99s the best science we have today. It=E2=
=80=99s more likely that this is essentially the way the world works than n=
ot. Our intuitions based on lived experience have misled us before.=C2=A0
People believed that the Earth was flat, until Ancient Greek scientists pro=
ved it was round (unless you=E2=80=99re Kyrie [https://email.mg2.substack.c=
om/c/eJxFUUuu5CAMPE1nRxQI-S1YvM27RmSI00FNIAKnZ3L7cXcWI1mA7DJlVzkgfKZ8mSMVqj=
